subject: Add kernel and user CPU utilization
commitMessage:
Add kernel and user CPU utilization

This adds two utilization sensors, "CPU_Kernel" and "CPU_User" that
are populated with the fraction of CPU processing spent in kernel space
and user space.

The intended use case is BMCWeb can read those sensors from
phosphor-health-monitor and report them in a RedFish response.

The RedFish resources are:
* ManagerDiagnosticData.ProcessorStatistics.KernelPercent
* ManagerDiagnosticData.ProcessorStatistics.UserPercent

Tested: Installed on a QEMU-emulated BMC
bmc# busctl tree xyz.openbmc_project.HealthMon
`-/xyz
  `-/xyz/openbmc_project
    `-/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors
      `-/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/utilization
        |-/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/utilization/CPU
        |-/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/utilization/CPU_Kernel
        `-/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/utilization/CPU_User

signed-off-by: Sui Chen <suichen@google.com>
Change-Id: Ic6792e4c7cd8eba144eb9adec9366c1bc15b1a44

Is this change require? as we are making changes 2 places. And it is better to define constant

Yes it is needed, the reason is we need Kernel CPU usage and User CPU usage to be separate sensors for usage with the newly-proposed ManagerDiagnosticData Redfish schema, and it should be good if they look similar to existing ones (there are existing kernel percent and user percent in Redfish: https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/ProcessorMetrics_v1.xml )

Do you have suggestions for good names for "CPU_Kernel" and "CPU_User"?

Update: switching to using associations, so the DBus object names should not matter now, and should not be used to determine that this utilization sensor is about the BMC rather than the host. The utilization sensors are now to be found by following the associations.
